  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Corruption\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies\n- Mandatory transaction reporting\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious activity monitoring\n- Financial institution compliance programs\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Substantial fines for non-compliance\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Regulated Sectors\n- Banking\n- Financial services\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Real estate\n- Casino and gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes by establishing comprehensive regulatory standards and enforcement protocols.",
